The paper proposes a novel strategy for constructing a random Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for time series forecasting, which involves the iterative addition of random filters and neurons to the error-feedback fully connected layer. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories, as it deals with the design and tuning of neural network architectures. Additionally, the paper involves the use of CNNs, which are commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) tasks, and the proposed strategy involves the selection of filters, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper involves the use of stochastic methods and incremental learning, which are relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
